",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T05:11:22.750Z\",\"uuid\":\"b9002b52-0d48-4ff8-91fe-a91962bd1715\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cf3f8b42-d3cd-46bd-bfd0-b1ccf0e2a093\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"b3d2dd85-97f1-4a42-bb85-d5ddb6f44882\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-explain-missing-multisession-prompt\",\"slug\":\"luminous-foraging-giraffe\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Us12trjMw7DLq6LXB8q3Px\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# `entire explain` bugs\\n     2→\\n     3→## Bug 1: \\\"(no prompt)\\\" in list view\\n     4→\\n     5→`ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` only reads the latest session's `prompt.txt`.\\n     6→When the latest session has no prompt (e.g. a test session condensed alongside a real one),\\n     7→it returns `\\\"\\\"` and the list view shows `(no prompt)`.\\n     8→\\n     9→**Fix:** Fall back through earlier sessions when the latest has no prompt.\\n    10→\\n    11→**Files:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:546` (`ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree`)\\n    12→\\n    13→## Bug 2: Wrong author in detail view\\n    14→\\n    15→`GetCheckpointAuthor` walks `entire/checkpoints/v1` commit history to find the commit that\\n    16→introduced the checkpoint's `metadata.json`. This is broken:\\n    17→\\n    18→1. The tree is cumulative — every commit after creation has the file, so it walks thousands of commits\\n    19→2. `LogOrderCommitterTime` with multi-timezone authors creates unpredictable walk order\\n    20→3. In worktrees, go-git may resolve the branch ref incorrectly (packed-refs vs loose refs mismatch)\\n    21→4. Even when it works, it returns the git identity of whoever ran the CLI that condensed, not the session author\\n    22→\\n    23→**Observed:** Returns `Sven Pfleiderer` for Alex's checkpoint because the walk stops at the wrong boundary.\\n    24→\\n    25→**Fix:** Use the associated commit's author (from the user's branch) instead. `getAssociatedCommits()`\\n    26→already computes this at `explain.go:293` — use the first commit's author.\\n    27→\\n    28→**Files:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1614` (`GetCheckpointAuthor`), `cmd/entire/cli/explain.go:290`\\n    29→\\n    30→## Bug 3: Test session leaking into real checkpoint data\\n    31→\\n    32→Checkpoint `629ded414de3` has two sessions:\\n    33→- Session 0: Alex's real Claude Code session (UUID session ID, has prompt, has tokens)\\n    34→- Session 1: `session_id: \\\"test\\\"`, `agent: \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\"`, no prompt, no transcript\\n    35→\\n    36→Both were condensed from the same shadow branch `entire/aaeab8f-d4735e` during the same\\n    37→PostCommit hook execution. The test session had a `.git/entire-sessions/test.json` state file\\n    38→with matching `WorktreePath` and `BaseCommit`.\\n    39→\\n    40→**Root cause:** The `TestDispatchLifecycleEvent_RoutesToCorrectHandler` test's **SubagentEnd**\\n    41→case creates `test.json` whenever the working tree has untracked files.\\n    42→\\n    43→The chain:\\n    44→\\n    45→1. SubagentEnd test case runs with `sessionID: \\\"test\\\"` and no `t.Chdir()` — real CWD\\n    46→2. `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd` calls `DetectFileChanges(ctx, nil)` — nil preUntrackedFiles\\n    47→   because `LoadPreTaskState` fails (no pre-task state was captured for this fake event)\\n    48→3. With nil preUntrackedFiles, every untracked file in the working tree is reported as \\\"New\\\"\\n    49→   (only `.entire/` paths are filtered by `IsInfrastructurePath`)\\n    50→4. Non-empty file change list → handler calls `SaveTaskStep` with `AgentType: ag.Type()`\\n    51→   → `\\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\"` (from `newMockAgent()`)\\n    52→5. `SaveTaskStep` (`manual_commit_git.go:176`) finds no session state for \\\"test\\\" → calls\\n    53→   `initializeSession(\\\"test\\\", \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\", ...)` as fallback\\n    54→6. `test.json` is written to `.git/entire-sessions/` with fresh `started_at` and `turn_id`\\n    55→\\n    56→**Why it affects everyone:** Every developer has untracked files (temp files, `.DS_Store`,\\n    57→editor swap files, `tmp/` contents). Any non-`.entire/` untracked file triggers the chain.\\n    58→\\n    59→**Why it gets recreated:** Each test run overwrites the file via `initializeSession` (fresh\\n    60→`started_at`, fresh `turn_id`). The Compaction test case then maintains it by updating\\n    61→`last_interaction_time`.\\n    62→\\n    63→**Maintenance (ongoing):** Two mechanisms keep the file alive between recreations:\\n    64→- **Compaction test:** Same dispatch test's Compaction case runs with `sessionID: \\\"test\\\"` from\\n    65→  real CWD — loads existing `test.json`, transitions phase, saves back, updating\\n    66→  `last_interaction_time`.\\n    67→- **PostCommit hook:** `findSessionsForWorktree` matches `test.json` by `WorktreePath` on\\n    68→  every real commit. Condenses it alongside real sessions, sets `files_touched` and\\n    69→  `last_checkpoint_id`.\\n    70→\\n    71→**Reproduction:**\\n    72→\\n    73→```bash\\n    74→# Create any untracked file in the worktree\\n    75→echo \\\"trigger\\\" > untracked-trigger.txt\\n    76→\\n    77→# Run the SubagentEnd dispatch test\\n    78→go test -count=1 -run 'TestDispatchLifecycleEvent_RoutesToCorrectHandler/SubagentEnd' ./cmd/entire/cli/\\n    79→\\n    80→# Verify test.json was created\\n    81→cat .git/entire-sessions/test.json\\n    82→# → session_id: \\\"test\\\", agent_type: \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\", files_touched: [\\\"untracked-trigger.txt\\\"]\\n    83→\\n    84→# Clean up\\n    85→rm untracked-trigger.txt .git/entire-sessions/test.json\\n    86→```\\n    87→\\n    88→**Fix:**\\n    89→1. Fix the dispatch test: add `t.Chdir(t.TempDir())` to SubagentEnd and Compaction cases\\n    90→   (or the entire test) so they don't touch real repo state\\n    91→2. Delete `.git/entire-sessions/test.json` on all developer machines\\n    92→3. Add defensive filtering: skip sessions with non-UUID `session_id` during condensation\\n    93→4. Consider `entire clean` check for suspicious session IDs\\n    94→\\n    95→**Impact:** Bugs 1 and 2 are symptoms — the test session becomes the \\\"latest\\\" session in\\n    96→multi-session checkpoints, masking the real session's prompt and metadata.\\n    97→\\n    98→**Scope:** 147 contaminated checkpoints on `entire/checkpoints/v1` across 57 branches,\\n    99→all with `session_id: \\\"test\\\"` and `agent: \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\"`.\\n   100→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"8b290437-418b-4427-808d-7ae5e9d58479\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T05:11:22.749Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-03-05-explain-bugs.md\",\"content\":\"# `entire explain` bugs\\n\\n## Bug 1: \\\"(no prompt)\\\" in list view\\n\\n`ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` only reads the latest session's `prompt.txt`.\\nWhen the latest session has no prompt (e.g. a test session condensed alongside a real one),\\nit returns `\\\"\\\"` and the list view shows `(no prompt)`.\\n\\n**Fix:** Fall back through earlier sessions when the latest has no prompt.\\n\\n**Files:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:546` (`ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree`)\\n\\n## Bug 2: Wrong author in detail view\\n\\n`GetCheckpointAuthor` walks `entire/checkpoints/v1` commit history to find the commit that\\nintroduced the checkpoint's `metadata.json`. This is broken:\\n\\n1. The tree is cumulative — every commit after creation has the file, so it walks thousands of commits\\n2. `LogOrderCommitterTime` with multi-timezone authors creates unpredictable walk order\\n3. In worktrees, go-git may resolve the branch ref incorrectly (packed-refs vs loose refs mismatch)\\n4. Even when it works, it returns the git identity of whoever ran the CLI that condensed, not the session author\\n\\n**Observed:** Returns `Sven Pfleiderer` for Alex's checkpoint because the walk stops at the wrong boundary.\\n\\n**Fix:** Use the associated commit's author (from the user's branch) instead. `getAssociatedCommits()`\\nalready computes this at `explain.go:293` — use the first commit's author.\\n\\n**Files:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1614` (`GetCheckpointAuthor`), `cmd/entire/cli/explain.go:290`\\n\\n## Bug 3: Test session leaking into real checkpoint data\\n\\nCheckpoint `629ded414de3` has two sessions:\\n- Session 0: Alex's real Claude Code session (UUID session ID, has prompt, has tokens)\\n- Session 1: `session_id: \\\"test\\\"`, `agent: \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\"`, no prompt, no transcript\\n\\nBoth were condensed from the same shadow branch `entire/aaeab8f-d4735e` during the same\\nPostCommit hook execution. The test session had a `.git/entire-sessions/test.json` state file\\nwith matching `WorktreePath` and `BaseCommit`.\\n\\n**Root cause:** The `TestDispatchLifecycleEvent_RoutesToCorrectHandler` test's **SubagentEnd**\\ncase creates `test.json` whenever the working tree has untracked files.\\n\\nThe chain:\\n\\n1. SubagentEnd test case runs with `sessionID: \\\"test\\\"` and no `t.Chdir()` — real CWD\\n2. `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd` calls `DetectFileChanges(ctx, nil)` — nil preUntrackedFiles\\n   because `LoadPreTaskState` fails (no pre-task state was captured for this fake event)\\n3. With nil preUntrackedFiles, every untracked file in the working tree is reported as \\\"New\\\"\\n   (only `.entire/` paths are filtered by `IsInfrastructurePath`)\\n4. Non-empty file change list → handler calls `SaveTaskStep` with `AgentType: ag.Type()`\\n   → `\\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\"` (from `newMockAgent()`)\\n5. `SaveTaskStep` (`manual_commit_git.go:176`) finds no session state for \\\"test\\\" → calls\\n   `initializeSession(\\\"test\\\", \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\", ...)` as fallback\\n6. `test.json` is written to `.git/entire-sessions/` with fresh `started_at` and `turn_id`\\n\\n**Why it affects everyone:** Every developer has untracked files (temp files, `.DS_Store`,\\neditor swap files, `tmp/` contents). Any non-`.entire/` untracked file triggers the chain.\\n\\n**Why it gets recreated:** Each test run overwrites the file via `initializeSession` (fresh\\n`started_at`, fresh `turn_id`). The Compaction test case then maintains it by updating\\n`last_interaction_time`.\\n\\n**Maintenance (ongoing):** Two mechanisms keep the file alive between recreations:\\n- **Compaction test:** Same dispatch test's Compaction case runs with `sessionID: \\\"test\\\"` from\\n  real CWD — loads existing `test.json`, transitions phase, saves back, updating\\n  `last_interaction_time`.\\n- **PostCommit hook:** `findSessionsForWorktree` matches `test.json` by `WorktreePath` on\\n  every real commit. Condenses it alongside real sessions, sets `files_touched` and\\n  `last_checkpoint_id`.\\n\\n**Reproduction:**\\n\\n```bash\\n# Create any untracked file in the worktree\\necho \\\"trigger\\\" > untracked-trigger.txt\\n\\n# Run the SubagentEnd dispatch test\\ngo test -count=1 -run 'TestDispatchLifecycleEvent_RoutesToCorrectHandler/SubagentEnd' ./cmd/entire/cli/\\n\\n# Verify test.json was created\\ncat .git/entire-sessions/test.json\\n# → session_id: \\\"test\\\", agent_type: \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\", files_touched: [\\\"untracked-trigger.txt\\\"]\\n\\n# Clean up\\nrm untracked-trigger.txt .git/entire-sessions/test.json\\n```\\n\\n**Fix:**\\n1. Fix the dispatch test: add `t.Chdir(t.TempDir())` to SubagentEnd and Compaction cases\\n   (or the entire test) so they don't touch real repo state\\n2. Delete `.git/entire-sessions/test.json` on all developer machines\\n3. Add defensive filtering: skip sessions with non-UUID `session_id` during condensation\\n4. Consider `entire clean` check for suspicious session IDs\\n\\n**Impact:** Bugs 1 and 2 are symptoms — the test session becomes the \\\"latest\\\" session in\\nmulti-session checkpoints, masking the real session's prompt and metadata.\\n\\n**Scope:** 147 contaminated checkpoints on `entire/checkpoints/v1` across 57 branches,\\nall with `session_id: \\\"test\\\"` and `agent: \\\"Mock Lifecycle Agent\\\"`.\\n\",\"numLines\":100,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":100}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"cf3f8b42-d3cd-46bd-bfd0-b1ccf0e2a093\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8b290437-418b-4427-808d-7ae5e9d58479\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"b3d2dd85-97f1-4a42-bb85-d5ddb6f44882\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-explain-missing-multisession-prompt\",\"slug\":\"luminous-foraging-giraffe\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014AaXzgZRx2X2VxSCSFyrYP\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I understand the bug. Let me look at the relevant files to understand the fix needed.\\n\\nThe bug is that the `TestDispatchLifecycleEvent_RoutesToCorrectHandler` test's SubagentEnd case creates a `test.json` session state file in the real `.git/entire-sessions/` directory because it doesn't use `t.Chdir()` to isolate itself.\\n\\nLet me look at the test file and the relevant code.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1905,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":19236,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1905},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYmFZwuWiofA3skBeBBWi\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"edc9ee3b-928a-482b-8a1e-e5c3dc2be85f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T05:11:26.110Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"edc9ee3b-928a-482b-8a1e-e5c3dc2be85f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"b3d2dd85-97f1-4a42-bb85-d5ddb6f44882\",\